<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12167f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12167f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12167f"> 167(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Wattle Bridge Ulst / Berehaven (cromlech) / dallans</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">AN IRELAND OF THE CONTINENT / WHERE CELTIC CLANS MEET / &hellip; / The Irish delegates to the gathering of the Celtic clans at Quimper will find themselves at home among the Bretons. / &hellip; Rude monuments of a high antiquity, closely akin to those found scattered over Ireland, survive abundantly throughout the province: cromlechs in plenty, dolmens, <mark>dallans</mark>, the so-called Druid&apos;s altar, and the great stone circle, whence, in the pagan dawn, belts of flame leapt up to glorify the Sun, even as at <mark>Wattle Bridge</mark> in Ulster, or <mark>Berehaven</mark> in the far south <font color="green">[in Cork]</font>. <small> <a name="II19sep24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#II19sep24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (19 September 1924) 6/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
